Package es.weso.asio.ontology.test.manifest.impl

Class ManifestParserImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.weso.asio.ontology.test.manifest.impl.ManifestParserImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ManifestParser
    public class ManifestParserImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements ManifestParser
    The manifest parser reads a manifest file and extracts the array of test cases that it defines. It is composed by a default constructor that takes the path to the manifest file and a getTestCases method that parses the given file and returns an array of test cases.

    • Constructor Detail

      • ManifestParserImpl

        public ManifestParserImpl​(java.lang.String manifestFilePath)
                   throws java.io.FileNotFoundException
        Default constructor for the manifest parser, from the manifest file path it creates a new file reader that will be later used to access to the file content. If the given manifest file path points to an existing file the constructor will throw a file not found exception.
        Parameters:
        manifestFilePath - is the file path to the manifest file.
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - if the manifest file path given does not exists.

    • Method Detail

      • getTestCases

        public TestCase[] getTestCases()
        Gets an array composed by the test cases declared in the manifest file. For that aim it instantiate a Google JSON object that will parse the file and create the array containing the test cases. It is implemented by using laze initialization so that the test cases array is computed only the first time. Other accesses to the variable will not trigger the execution of the Google JSON parser.

        getTestCases in interface ManifestParser
